headline.main: WEYGAND'S ECLIPSE A BLOW TO ALLIES; But We Await Proof That Nazis Will Have Own Way in Vichy

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 22 -- The "retirement" of General Maxime Weygand as leader of the French Empire in Africa has produced about as many vague and conflicting interpretations as a patient public will stand, but everybody seems to be agreed on at least one point: this development bodes no good for the democracies.
abstract: effect of Weygand ouster on democracies discussed
